 number, of order twice the denominator. There is also an\nelliptic analogue of the Riemann-Hilbert correspondence: an analytic\nequivalence between categories of elliptic difference equations, swapping the\nrole of the shift of the equation and the nome of the curve.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 29 Jul 2016 17:51:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 8 Aug 2016 00:45:05 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 12 Sep 2017 19:50:19 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 29 Jul 2019 16:58:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-30"}
