ple phases, we obtain a precise dayside hemisphere H2O\nabundance ($2.5\\times 10^{-5} - 1.1\\times 10^{-4}$ at 1$\\sigma$ confidence)\nand, assuming chemical equilibrium and a scaled solar abundance pattern, we\nderive a corresponding metallicity estimate that is consistent with being solar\n(0.4 -- 1.7). Using the retrieved global CO+CO2 abundance under the same\nassumptions, we estimate a comparable metallicity of 0.3 - 1.7$\\times$ solar.\n(Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 30 Jul 2016 01:06:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 30 Dec 2016 05:54:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-13"}
